HEADWORD: Semiotic
<hw>Se`mi*ot"ic</hw> }</mhw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>shmeiwtiko`s</grk>, fr. <grk>shmei^on</grk> a mark, a sign.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Relating to signs or indications; pertaining to the
language of signs, or to language generally as indicating
thought.</def>⟦br⟧
